      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and required by FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. Each QoI maps to a clinically relevant failure mode: excessive flexibility (stiffness), permanent deformation onset (yield force), and ultimate structural integrity (40 mm force). Gradation 3 achieved."
