    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is judged acceptable given the conservative and standardized nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol and the medium model risk level. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) are satisfied for all three primary QoIs. The credibility evidence package is accepted in support of the 510(k) submission. Note: final laboratory report data were incorporated into validation result nodes after the package signature timestamp; the package was not re-signed following this update.",
